"It's going to be a big season first and foremost, and then hopefully we're in the Premier League next season as well.
"It's a massive two years, but I'm excited for it and I'm feeling good going into it."
Meanwhile, Hull have signed Wimbledon goalkeeper Will Mannion, 18, on a three-year deal, with a compensation fee set to be decided by a tribunal.
Mannion has yet to make a senior appearance, and will play for Hull's under-21 side next season.
